    skos:definition "Viking Age art style (c. 850–950) named after finds from the Borre ship burial mound in Vestfold, Norway. Characterized by ring-chain interlace, gripping beasts, and backward-looking animal heads. Widespread across the Viking world."@en ;
    skos:broader ni:viking-art-styles .

