    skos:definition "Viking Age art style (c. 900–975) named after the Jelling royal monuments in Denmark. Features S-shaped ribbon animals with open interlace, pigtail-like extensions, and head seen in profile. Prominent on the Jelling cup and smaller Jelling stone."@en ;
    skos:broader ni:viking-art-styles .

# ── 122/161: Mammen style ──
