    skos:definition "Viking Age art style (c. 960–1020) named after a decorated axe head from Mammen, Jutland. Features bold, semi-naturalistic animals with double-contoured bodies filled with pelleting and plant tendrils. The great beast on the Jelling stone is Mammen style."@en ;
    skos:broader ni:viking-art-styles .

