    skos:definition "The last Viking Age art style (c. 1050–1150), named after the carved wooden panels of Urnes stave church in Sogn, Norway. Features elegant, asymmetrical animal interlace with figure-eight loops and extremely attenuated animal forms. Bridges into Romanesque art."@en ;
    skos:broader ni:viking-art-styles .

